other_tests.findings: Patient 1: Homozygous missense mutation c.444C>A predicting amino acid exchange of asparagine at codon 148 with lysine (p.N148K). Patient 2: Homozygous missense mutation c.383A>G and a small insertion c.384-385insCT.
Small gonads in the inguinal canal were removed. The excised gonads showed relatively small, oval seminiferous tubular outlines without basal lamina thickening and no interstitial fibrosis.
Excised gonads exhibited small, oval seminiferous tubular outlines without basal lamina thickening and no interstitial fibrosis. Leydig cells were not visible.
